<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1445,1758]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,402,1445,1470]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">Diagnostic character</emphasis>
: presence of spongy structures covering the parameres, parameres with setae on its apex (
<figureCitation box="[159,291,1481,1506]" captionStart="FIGURE 5 A – F" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1589,1611]" captionTargetBox="[336,1251,199,1555]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[324,1264,193,1567]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 5 A – F. Male genitalia of Macrelmis. A, B: alea sp. group. A. M. alea. B. M. aeolis (both modified from Hinton, 1946). C, D. milleri sp. group. C. M. milleri. D. M. hayakae (both modified from Spangler, 1997). E, F. clypeata sp. group. E. M. clypeata. F. M isus (modified from Hinton, 1946). Scale bars: A, B, E, F: 0.1 mm; C: 0.3 mm; D: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241275/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">
Figs. 
<number box="[222,236,1481,1506]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" value="5.0">5</number>
A, B
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1445,1758]" box="[199,1132,1517,1542]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1517,1542]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">Species:</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[302,594,1517,1541]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">
<taxonomicName box="[302,498,1517,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Macrelmis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeolis">Macrelmis aeolis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[509,594,1517,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Macrelmis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alea">M. alea</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[608,724,1517,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Macrelmis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="browni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[608,724,1517,1541]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">M. browni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[731,821,1517,1542]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,821,1517,1542]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[875,1035,1518,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Macrelmis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itatiaiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[875,1035,1518,1541]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">M. itatiaiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1042,1132,1517,1542]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1042,1132,1517,1542]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="201" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1445,1758]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,362,1553,1578]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">Distribution (</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[363,432,1553,1578]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1707,1729]" captionTargetBox="[320,1250,412,1664]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[320,1257,411,1668]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 6. Distributional map of South American species of Macrelmis. The question mark in the big map over Brazil represents M. antiqua, a species without a more precise location known. The question mark in frame B over São Paulo state represents M. salti, another species with not many detail, beside the state where it occurs in Brazil." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241276/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">
Fig. 
<number box="[415,432,1553,1578]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
): 
<collectingCountry box="[454,526,1553,1578]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[454,526,1553,1578]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">Brasil</emphasis>
</collectingCountry>
: Santa Catarina (
<bibRefCitation author="Hinton" box="[722,870,1553,1578]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" refString="Hinton, H. E. (1946) A synopsis of the Brazilian species of Elsianus Sharp (Coleoptera, Elmidae). Transaction of Royal of Entomological Soicety of London, 96 (8), 125 - 149. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1946. tb 00447. x" type="journal article" year="1946">
Hinton 
<number box="[810,870,1553,1578]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" value="1946.0">1946</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), Rio de Janeiro (present work) and Minas Gerais (present work).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1445,1758]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,452,1625,1650]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">History of the group</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[470,648,1625,1649]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Macrelmis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alea">
<emphasis box="[470,648,1625,1649]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">Macrelmis alea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[709,817,1625,1649]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Macrelmis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeolis">
<emphasis box="[709,817,1625,1649]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">M. aeolis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were considered as closely related by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hinton" box="[1273,1436,1625,1650]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" refString="Hinton, H. E. (1946) A synopsis of the Brazilian species of Elsianus Sharp (Coleoptera, Elmidae). Transaction of Royal of Entomological Soicety of London, 96 (8), 125 - 149. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1946. tb 00447. x" type="journal article" year="1946">
Hinton (
<number box="[1369,1427,1625,1650]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" value="1946.0">1946</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
based on the presence of spongy structure, presence of head granulation and shape of fifth abdominal sternite, but a species group has never been formally proposed. In addition to these two species, 
<taxonomicName box="[1088,1249,1698,1721]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Macrelmis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itatiaiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1088,1249,1698,1721]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">M. itatiaiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1258,1349,1697,1722]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1258,1349,1697,1722]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Macrelmis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="browni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">M. browni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[236,326,1733,1758]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[236,326,1733,1758]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
also have the defining characters and are added to the group.
</paragraph>
